===Talking to a man or woman around Lumbridge===
* '''Man:''' Eeek! What is it?
* '''Zanik:''' I'm Zanik of the Dorgeshuun!
* '''Man:''' A cave goblin? Well, there goes the neighbourhood!
* '''Player:''' What do you mean?
* '''Man:''' It's all very well the duke signing a peace treaty with those creatures. Maybe that'll stop them attacking us.
* '''Man:''' But for them to come wandering around the surface and mixing with decent people? I don't know, what's the world coming to?
* '''Zanik:''' We were never going to attack you! YOU nearly attacked US!
* '''Man:''' Oh, they may say they're civilised, but they're still goblins. You can't trust them. The only reason they're not a threat is that they're so stupid.
* '''Zanik:''' Stop talking about me like I'm not here!
* {{tact|end}}

====Talking to a man or woman again====
* {{trandom}}
* {{topt|Dialogue 1}}
** '''Man:''' Keep away from me you dirty goblin!
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Dialogue 2}}
** '''Man:''' I don't know, what will be next? Cave goblins LIVING up here? Taking our jobs? I wouldn't want my daughter to marry a goblin!
** '''Zanik:''' I'm not sure a Dorgeshuun would want to marry a human!
** '''Man:''' What rudeness! This is why they say goblins have no manners!
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Dialogue 3}}
** '''Man:''' Oh, I've got nothing against goblins in their own place. I just don't think they ought to be wandering around in our city and making the place look bad.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Dialogue 4}}
** '''Man:''' Goblins wandering around Lumbridge and talking to the duke like they're normal people? I don't know what the world's coming to.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Dialogue 5}}
** '''Man:''' It just makes me uncomfortable, is all. What if I was in bed and some horrible little goblin poked its head up through the floor?
** '''Zanik:''' We would never do that! We don't tunnel upwards and we're very careful not to damage human cellars.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Dialogue 6}}
** '''Man:''' You cave goblins... don't you, you know, eat people?
** '''Zanik:''' No!
** '''Man:''' Oh! Well, that's all right then.
** {{tact|end}}

===Duke Horacio===
* '''Duke Horacio:''' Greetings. Welcome to my castle.
* '''Duke Horacio:''' It's good to see a visitor from the Dorgeshuun! I am Duke Horacio.
* '''Zanik:''' I'm Zanik of the Dorgeshuun! Headman Ur-Tag sends his greetings.
* '''Duke Horacio:''' Tell Ur-Tag that I wish to speak with him again. I think that our cities could profit from trading with one another, but there can be little trade if he does not allow visitors to enter the city.
* '''Zanik:''' I know! But the ruling council is so slow to make decisions. It's made up of old fogeys who are set in their ways.
* '''Duke Horacio:''' Now then, child, there is room for caution and experience in politics.
* '''Zanik:''' Maybe when I return I can convince them to open the gates of the city.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|I'd like to get into the city too.}}
** '''Player:''' I'd like to get into the city too.
** '''Zanik:''' I wish I could show it to you, [player name]!
** '''Zanik:''' Someday I will, but I don't think the council will agree to open the doors any time soon.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Tell me about the treaty.}}
** '''Player:''' Tell me about the treaty.
** '''Duke Horacio:''' It basically defines the borders between our two societies. It's not usual for two states to be above one another rather than side-by-side!
** '''Duke Horacio:''' Everything above ground, within the borders of Lumbridge, belongs to Lumbridge. Everything below ground belongs to the Dorgeshuun. Except for the cellars of our buildings, those belong to Lumbridge.
** '''Duke Horacio:''' Of course both our underground systems might expand. Neither state can build new tunnels that are too close to the other's systems...
** '''Zanik:''' This is boring. Let's go.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Have you heard of any HAM activity lately?}}
** '''Player:''' Have you heard of any HAM activity lately?
** '''Duke Horacio:''' No... I know they've been gaining members but I haven't heard anything else from them. They may be planning something, but then again they may not.
** {{tact|end}}

